result.execSummary:
The defendant Caleb Wesley Allan Dykema was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting/Failing to Stop/Fleeing, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.04(2t).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Case called at 10:38am [ma]
Defendant Caleb Wesley Allan Dykema in court with Attorney Robert Franklin Nagel.  Susan Victoria Happ appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Atty. Nagel indicates that he would like to an opportunity to speak with assigned prosecutor.

The Court will recall case at 11:15am
recess: 10:41am--reconvene:11:37am

Defendant Caleb Wesley Allan Dykema in court with Attorney Robert Franklin Nagel.  ADA Brookellen Teuber appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Atty. Nagel admits service and waives reading of the Amended Information
ADA Teuber verifies victim rights compliance

The Court approves the amendment of the charge

Maximum penalties recited; Constitutional rights reviewed; plea of " GUILTY " entered to the charge in the Amended Information; factual basis stipulated; the Court accepts the plea, finds Defendant guilty, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.

Sentencing arguments given by Counsel
Statement made by Mr. Dykema

The Court withholds sentence, and places Defendant on Probation for 1 year, with conditions:

--to serve 30 days in the County Jail, with Huber/work-release privileges, to commence on 10/17/16 by 6:00 pm.
--The Court does authorize transfer to Grant County, so long as it is served as would be in Jefferson County, that is without electronic monitoring
---Mr. Dykema is required to report for commencement and service of jail sentence with absolute sobriety and without non-prescribed controlled substances in system; non-compliance will result in loss of work-release privileges without further process.

--to undergo any assessment, treatment or counseling as deemed appropriate by the Agent
--to attempt to obtain/maintain employment and/or education program as approved by the Agent
--provide DNA sample
--to pay statutory costs

The Court revokes Mr. Dykema's driver's license for 6 month, effective 10/12/2016

The Court does NOT allow expungment of this case
